Named after the ancient marketplaces of the world, an exchange was a place where communities with different resources could meet and trade to fulfill needs while also sharing their culture, history, wares and ideas. In that way, the Lealman Exchange is a collection of resources for the Lealman Community and greater Pinellas County. It is a place where local resources and service providers can come together to bring residents what they need. The Lealman Exchange, or LEX, is a community center celebrating Lealman pride. We are a public/private partnership between Pinellas County and the St. Petersburg Foundation.  We and our tenants share one goal: building a better tomorrow within the Lealman Community. We achieve this goal through: Community Impact Partnerships Public Programs Shared Resources We welcome you to stop by the center for an open gym, to find support services, or to host your next event! OUR MISSION Celebrating Lealman pride and increasing opportunities through partnerships and programs focused on economic empowerment, educational advancement, health & wellness, character & leadership and community connectivity. OUR VISION Helping the community members of Lealman have a better life and a better tomorrow. A Place to Connect Our goal is to connect Lealman residents with services in job training, education, health and wellness, economic empowerment and leadership. Our campus is located next to Raymond Neri Park. It includes a gymnasium, classrooms, and office space. Currently, LEX tenants include: YMCA Preschool Academy – For children ages 2 months – 5 years. YMCA of Greater St. Petersburg Sports – Open gym, drop-in adult basketball and pickleball, youth basketball. YMCA Community Health Programming – SilverSneakers® classes, Parkinson’s Disease Programs, Fall Prevention Programs. YReads! Program – Providing kindergarten through 8th grade students with the intensive reading instruction they need to succeed. AmSkills – Tech and manufacturing training and job placement programs. Community Tampa Bay – Provider of the ANYTOWN Program.  Educating and cultivated inclusive leaders. Family Center on Deafness – Empowering Pinellas County’s Deaf Community by providing opportunities to enhance communication, education, and independence. Wounded Warriors Abilities Ranch – Inspiring veterans to get out and active.  Facilitates open gym hours for adaptive sports. CES Academy – Charter school. Pinellas Public Library – Apply for a library card, access the library network to reserve materials, pick up and drop off library books, and take advantage of the free lending library for children. UF / IFAS Extension – Local branch of a nationwide network of land grant universities providing non-biased, research-based  information to America’s citizens. Pinellas County – Lealman Community Redevelopment Area (CRA) staff provide support to other County services and a variety of residential and commercial redevelopment grant programs. St. Petersburg Foundation – A social impact consultancy building capacity at the organizational and community level.
